==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sistrum
<hw>Sis"trum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/, from
<?/<?/<?/ to shake.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An instrument
consisting of a thin metal frame, through which passed a number of metal
rods, and furnished with a handle by which it was shaken and made to
rattle. It was peculiarly Egyptian, and used especially in the worship
of Isis. It is still used in Nubia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sisyphean</ent>⟦br⟧
